import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['ret'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Daily Returns')
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['ret'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Daily Returns')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily returns?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.scatter(data['open'], data['close'], label='Open vs Close')
    plt.xlabel('Open Price')
    plt.ylabel('Close Price')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between open and close prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    avg_daily_return = data.groupby('signal')['ret'].mean()
    ax = avg_daily_return.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green'])
    
    plt.title('What is the average daily return for each signal type?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Signal Type')
    plt.ylabel('Average Daily Return')
    
    for i, v in enumerate(avg_daily_return):
        ax.text(i - 0.1, v + 0.01, f"{v:.2f}", color='black', fontweight='bold')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data['high'], data['low']], labels=['High', 'Low'])
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of daily highs and lows?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.legend(['High', 'Low'], loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.title('What is the trend of the stock price over time?', wrap=True)
